I mean the first movie Peter was so obsessed with her still despite having the ability to go out with any girl in the school so he plotted the whole relationship with LJ. I know the kiss was meant to be the realisation that she wanted Peter still but like if she were that sure after it how come the whole movie is about her being confused? snippet.textDisplay:
I'll be honest Lara jean was the real jerk not Peter. He did lie about certain things about Jen, but only because he knew Lara Jean would misinterpret it to the fullest extent. Lara Jean tho made excuses to not only both the boys ,but to herself why she couldn't be honest about her feelings. Throughout the movie tho, we also learn that Lara has an unrealistic view of what love actually is. She's not actually ready or deserving to date either one when you think about it. 

Also, I think the writers intentionally made Peter to seem bad because in the first movie he was soo much better. Of course, he was still hung up on Jen, but that's normal when you recently broke up with someone. So you can't blame him entirely in this movie since Lara is constantly lying and not communicating with him. Overall, I think this movie has some good points, but I think the fact so many fans supported John Ambrose x Lara Jean is kind of bad. Love isn't a fleeting emotion.. it takes communication, trust, and commitment. (Among other things). Something Lara Jean clearly doesn't understand. I know some people say the book is different, and I am only judging the movie.
snippet.textOriginal:
I'll be honest Lara jean was the real jerk not Peter. He did lie about certain things about Jen, but only because he knew Lara Jean would misinterpret it to the fullest extent. Lara Jean tho made excuses to not only both the boys ,but to herself why she couldn't be honest about her feelings. Throughout the movie tho, we also learn that Lara has an unrealistic view of what love actually is. She's not actually ready or deserving to date either one when you think about it. 

Also, I think the writers intentionally made Peter to seem bad because in the first movie he was soo much better. Of course, he was still hung up on Jen, but that's normal when you recently broke up with someone. So you can't blame him entirely in this movie since Lara is constantly lying and not communicating with him. Overall, I think this movie has some good points, but I think the fact so many fans supported John Ambrose x Lara Jean is kind of bad. Love isn't a fleeting emotion.. it takes communication, trust, and commitment. (Among other things). Something Lara Jean clearly doesn't understand. I know some people say the book is different, and I am only judging the movie.
